    {
      "id": "gBQIkfjXcN7m0WPuR103g",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1624.3328053254154,
      "y": 461.05212356272943,
      "width": 1822.126708984375,
      "height": 1785,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0g",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2125513058,
      "version": 4693,
      "versionNonce": 1278696236,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1783608956795,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "next: \n\n- positive and negative controls: \n            Admin marks positions when registering the kit\n             Add controls statistics to the run QC report\n             ! Controls have to be excluded from the error rate estimates\n\n- Cross check primer plates - user cannot tick the same primer plates for different batches\n- !!!! if the job is running, you cannot submit the same kit\n\n- Consensus:\n            User can edit consensus file while checking the plots, edited genotypes are marked\n            Add table with genotype info, unaccepted alleles and stats\n            name page \"Sample report\"\n            Add per sample stats derived from consensus table\n\n- Add ? buttons with some instructions where needed\n- Request reanalysis button - send a message to admin with explanation of the reason\n- fix email notification - divja domain should be added as trusted in amazon\n\n\n- Add sex id - male or female\n\n- Mark stutters on the plots after consensus\n\nUsers: \n\n     Password restore for users\n      Ideally, we don't want to manuallu approve users.dr\n\n- Check the primers catalogue, all of the sets\n\n- Data storage - check for Glacier, and how many it costs \n- Look for reads for this kit on our server (make a button?) - or maybe add path to the kit data if reads are stored at the server?\n\nMake a glossary for terminology (sample batch, kit etc)\n\nCheck regulations for personal data database, make Terms and Conditions if needed\n\nPlan better DB architecture, improve kit tracking sistem\n\nSample mathing system - add unique ids to the samples (because users can add duplicated sample names)\n                               start with similarity matrix among all the samples from one project, then check the \n                                pairwise if similar enough. \n                                ADO are more often then false alleles. \n\n\n\n\n\n",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "next: \n\n- positive and negative controls: \n            Admin marks positions when registering the kit\n             Add controls statistics to the run QC report\n             ! Controls have to be excluded from the error rate estimates\n\n- Cross check primer plates - user cannot tick the same primer plates for different batches\n- !!!! if the job is running, you cannot submit the same kit\n\n- Consensus:\n            User can edit consensus file while checking the plots, edited genotypes are marked\n            Add table with genotype info, unaccepted alleles and stats\n            name page \"Sample report\"\n            Add per sample stats derived from consensus table\n\n- Add ? buttons with some instructions where needed\n- Request reanalysis button - send a message to admin with explanation of the reason\n- fix email notification - divja domain should be added as trusted in amazon\n\n\n- Add sex id - male or female\n\n- Mark stutters on the plots after consensus\n\nUsers: \n\n     Password restore for users\n      Ideally, we don't want to manuallu approve users.dr\n\n- Check the primers catalogue, all of the sets\n\n- Data storage - check for Glacier, and how many it costs \n- Look for reads for this kit on our server (make a button?) - or maybe add path to the kit data if reads are stored at the server?\n\nMake a glossary for terminology (sample batch, kit etc)\n\nCheck regulations for personal data database, make Terms and Conditions if needed\n\nPlan better DB architecture, improve kit tracking sistem\n\nSample mathing system - add unique ids to the samples (because users can add duplicated sample names)\n                               start with similarity matrix among all the samples from one project, then check the \n                                pairwise if similar enough. \n                                ADO are more often then false alleles. \n\n\n\n\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
